<p class=3DMsoNormal>&nbsp;</p>

<h3>46d - ENFORCEMENT PROCESS</h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>&nbsp;</p>

<h4>46d00 - Authority of WHD. </h4>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>&nbsp;</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-left:.25in'>Pursuant to the del=
egation
of authority from the Secretary of Homeland Security to the Secretary of La=
bor,
the WHD will, either pursuant to a complaint or otherwise, conduct
investigations to determine compliance with the H-2B requirements. In
connection with such investigations, WHD may enter any places, inspect any
records (and make transcriptions and copies thereof), question persons, and
gather any information deemed necessary to determine the status of complian=
ce. See
20 CFR 655.50(a) &amp; (b).</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>&nbsp;</p>

<h4>46d01 - Employer cooperation.</h4>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>&nbsp;</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-left:.25in'>An employer shall, =
at all
times, cooperate in administrative and enforcement proceedings. See 20 CFR
655.50(c). </p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>&nbsp;</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-indent:-.25in'>=
<span>(a)<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>An employ=
er
being investigated shall make available to the WHI: records, information,
persons and places as deemed appropriate to copy, transcribe, question, or
inspect.</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-left:.25in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-indent:-.25in'>=
<span>(b)<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>Where the
records are maintained at the central recordkeeping office, other than the
place or places of employment, such records must be made available for
inspection and copying within 72 hours following notice from the WHI.</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph>&nbsp;</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-indent:-.25in'>=
<span>(c)<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>H-2B empl=
oyers
are required to develop and maintain certain employment records to support
their compliance with the attestations made on the Application for Temporary
Employment Certification. These records include those specifically required=
 by
the H-2B program as well as those required by the FLSA for covered employer=
s,
including the following:</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph>&nbsp;</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'text-indent:-.25in'><span>(1)<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp; </span></span>Temporary need.=
 See 20
CFR 655.6(e).</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph>&nbsp;</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'text-indent:-.25in'><span>(2)<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp; </span></span>Determination o=
f the
prevailing wage. See 20 CFR 655.10(i).</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph>&nbsp;</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'text-indent:-.25in'><span>(3)<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp; </span></span>Pre-filing
recruitment, including newspaper advertisements. See 20 CFR 655.1.</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph>&nbsp;</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'text-indent:-.25in'><span>(4)<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp; </span></span>Recruitment rep=
ort
and evidence of U.S. worker referrals. See 20 CFR 655.16(j).</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph>&nbsp;</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'text-indent:-.25in'><span>(5)<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp; </span></span>Supporting evid=
ence
for temporary need. See 20 CFR 655.21(c).</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph>&nbsp;</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-left:.25in'>These records must =
be kept
for a period of no less than three years from the date of certification or =
from
the date of determination if the Application for Temporary Employment
Certification is denied or withdrawn, so they are available in the event th=
ey
are requested in an ETA request for further information (RFI) or audit, or a
WHD investigation.</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-indent:-.25in'>=
<span>(d)<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>No employ=
er or
representative or agent of an employer shall interfere with any official of=
 DOL
who is performing an investigation, inspection, or law enforcement function.
Any such interference shall be a violation of the Application for Temporary
Employment Certification and regulations. See 20 CFR 655.50(c).</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-left:.25in'>&nbsp;</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraph style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-indent:-.25in'>=
<span>(e)<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>The WHD s=
hall,
to the extent possible under existing law, protect the confidentiality of a=
ny
person who provides information in the course of an investigation. See 20 C=
FR 655.50(d).
</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>&nbsp;</p>

